#!/usr/bin/env perl
use warnings;
use strict;

use App::ZFSCurses;

=head1 NAME

zfscurses - create and run an App::ZFSCurses instance.

=cut

=head1 SYNOPSIS

zfscurses is a script to create and run an App::ZFSCurses instance.

=cut

App::ZFSCurses->new->run();

=head1 KEYSTROKES

Use the following keystrokes to navigate around the UI.

=over 4

=item Up/Down

Move the cursor up or down.

=item Enter/Space

Change focus around.

=item Ctrl+q

Quit the UI.

=item F1

When browsing a dataset properties, F1 will show a help message about the
selected property. You must first select a property using Enter/Space.

=back

=cut

